HELP=$"
lone	none	 	installed spells that are not being required"

LONG=$"
Installed spells that are not required
by any other installed spell are lone spells.
The lone command displays lone spells.
Removing lone spells that install libraries
may be useful increasing available disk space.
However, the lone command displays any lone spell
whether it installs programs or libraries.

The best way to remove installed software is
from the sorcery tool's dispel menu.
Run sorcery, goto spell menu, goto dispel menu.
That dispel menu displays menu after menu of lone spells
that can be selected for removal."

param(){ :;}

run(){ lone; }
